Title 1: About Us
Meta Description 1: I bring you greetings from the fascinating Family Medicine Residency Program of The Medical Center, Navicent Health/Mercer University School of Medicine. Since our inception in 1972, we have trained more than 270 family physicians. Our graduates are accomplished physicians in their communities. Surgeon General of the United States, Dr. Regina Bingaman, National Medical Association's 2013 Practitioner of the Year Award recipient Dr. Warren Hutchings, and numerous other community leaders are products of this stellar training program. The committed, dedicated, and highly qualified faculty and staff of this program create an environment conducive to learning and service with fellowship and fun.
